news.title: Group of ministers in favour of bare minimum GST on housing: Goa CM
news.para: This was one of the issues chiefly discussed in the (GoMs) meeting on Thursday, Sawant said. GoMs, Sawant said, also laid the thrust on the need to boost the real estate sector under GST.

news.title: BlackRock leases 42,700 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Worli
news.para: The financial institution’s India arm Blackrock Services India will be paying rental of Rs 325 per sq ft a month in the first year of the lease. The agreement includes a clause to escalate rentals by 5% in April 2025, by 10% a year after that and 5% each in 2027 and 2028.

news.title: Suraksha Group awards tenders for 41 towers of Jaypee Infratech projects
news.para: For the remaining 56 towers, Suraksha is expected to finalise contractors by Sept. This comes as a major relief to over 10,000 homebuyers who are waiting over a decade for their homes in various JIL projects.

news.title: SC orders YEIDA to address homebuyers' concerns amidst Jaypee Infratech dispute
news.para: While issuing notice to the monitoring committee of Jaypee Infratech Ltd on YEIDA’s appeal, Justice Khanna also asked the authority to inform if it had any scheme or a policy in place to ensure that flat buyers’ interests were protected.

news.title: Thirteen booked for irregularities worth Rs 200 crore in MHADA buildings' redevelopment plan
news.para: As per the FIR filed by Chitalsar police, a firm was given the contract to redevelop 18 buildings on land leased to these societies by the state run Maharashtra Housing and Area Development Authority, the official said.

news.title: Adani Group promoter sells 2.8% stake in Ambuja Cements for Rs 4,250 crore
news.para: Meanwhile, Rajiv Jain-backed GQG Partners purchased more than 4.39 crore shares, amounting to a 1.78 per cent stake in Ambuja Cements through bulk and block deals in two separate transactions.

news.title: China's Longfor Group plans further debt reductions this year
news.para: Beijing-based Longfor has fared better than many industry peers during the crisis because of its focus on larger cities, which have been recording stronger sales than those of smaller cities.

news.title: South Mumbai residents oppose additional security deposit on electricity bills
news.para: South Mumbai residents are resisting an extra security deposit added to electricity bills after smart meter installations. Former BMC opposition leader Ravi Raja has petitioned BEST to retract the charge and plans legal action.

news.title: Existing home sales in USA rise 1.3% in July 2024
news.para: Home resales, which account for a large portion of U.S. housing sales, declined 2.5% on a year-on-year basis in July. The median existing home price jumped 4.2% from a year earlier to $422,600. Home prices increased in all four U.S. regions.

news.title: Sebi bans Anil Ambani, 24 other entities for five years in fund diversion case
news.para: The regulator barred Reliance Home Finance from the securities market for six months and slapped a fine of Rs 6 lakh on it.

news.title: IndoSpace to invest over Rs 580 crore to develop two logistics parks in Karnataka
news.para: The parks, focused on industries like automobiles and electronics, will offer 1.8 million sq ft of development potential. IndoSpace currently operates three parks in Karnataka and has 52 nationwide, reflecting strong demand in the logistics sector.

news.title: Goa town planning department clears zone changes for 15 plots in three talukas
news.para: The TCP department will alter the RP 2021 using the Goa TCP Act’s Section 39A, which allows the department to change the zoning of a plot based on applications from the owners.

news.title: After 11 years, Chandigarh housing board to repair Dhanas colony
news.para: CHB has initiated the process to allot the work to a firm. The work, estimated to cost around Rs 71 lakh, will include repair of column beams, damaged flooring and dismantled plaster in the common areas of the buildings, including roof.

news.title: Fourth-floor policy on hold, Haryana government tells HC; next hearing on September 3
news.para: On July 2, Haryana decided to allow construction of four floors, a move that raised significant concerns over the city's infrastructure. Gurgaon Citizens Council (GCC), a residents' group, approached the high court challenging the policy.

news.title: Karnataka cabinet approves measures to address land valuation inconsistencies
news.para: The `12,690 crore project, costing about `705 crore per kilometre, will initially build an 18.5-kilometre double-decker tunnel.  A `9.45 crore detailed project report (DPR) is expected by September, after which tenders will be issued for construction.

news.title: Karnataka RERA appoints Rakesh Singh as its chairman
news.para: Singh has previously worked as the head of the water resources department, administrator for BBMP, and also as additional chief secretary of the urban development department (UDD).

news.title: Ciena leases 1.35 lakh sq ft space in TRIL Tower in Gurugram
news.para: "A lot of space that was part of the SEZ is getting denotified now, opening up newer areas for corporations," one of them said. "Tata also has a large portfolio under SEZ and is getting it denotified."

news.title: Ghaziabad: Raj Nagar Extension still waiting to get basics right
news.para: Today, those living in the area aren’t worried about inter-city connectivity. It’s the basics that they demand. From no water supply to bumpy roads, there’s a lot that needs to be developed here, residents say.

news.title: Asia Opportunities V sells 3% stake in PNB Housing for Rs 676 crore
news.para: ​As per the bulk deal data available on the BSE, Asia Opportunities V (Mauritius) divested 78 lakh shares or a 3 per cent stake in PNB Housing Finance at Rs 866.70 apiece, taking the deal value to Rs 676.02 crore.

news.title: Delhi: Over 1,100 people registered in two DDA housing schemes on first day
news.para: According to the officials, 750 people registered in Sasta Ghar Housing Scheme 2024, and 405 registered in DDA Madhyam Vargiya Housing Scheme 2024 on the first day of the registration on Thursday.
